column5: After being stuck in the house all day yesterday watching the rain come down, thinking it was here for the entire weekend, I was quite surprised to wake up and see stars in the sky and a let up with the wind gust  ......  Had a quick coffee, grabbed my gear and went out Muskie huntin' here on the river....  .....didn't take long before this fall fatty decided to  grab my crankbait and have some fun with me!....I landed her by 8:15AM....a few pike after that and then the winds picked up so I decided to head back to the house...    Sorry guys....decided to blur the background because of a few local lurkers that have been looking at this from another site
WTG Steve     She's a real beauty    Congratulation  Were you able to get measurements on her?  Looks very chunky Thanks for sharing Leechman
Awesome Steve     Been a long time coming since you hooked into one but you got rewarded today  Again great job Jacques aka Leechman

Absolutely fantastic fish Steve and even though you can't feel it,  I just gave you a pat on the back for that BIG brute  53 x 23 is a gorgeous big fish !!  I'll be south of you on the St. Lawrence for the next couple days and hope I get one even close to that beaut !!  Well done
Very nice fish, congrats. And on a pontoon boat, no less.  .
WTG, nice fatty for sure, gotta love the fall girth. You can tell how thick she is by your fingers barely stretching her skin, lol.

Man o man that's a beautiful fish Steve!!!  Big and fat and reaaaal purdy too!!!  It'll be a pleasure to update our tourney entrie with that one!!!   ... but there is one thing I don't like about it.......... I didn't catch it!  Congrats on a real "Killer" Musky!!!
Beautiful looking fish. Is that your PB?
That's a super chunky musky there! Like the wavy background as well. Congrats, ehg
real nice ski! Good work, thanks for sharing.
Wow!! Amazing fish!!!  I'll be sure to update the standings soon...it's gonna be close....  So lemme get this straight...it was 35 inches right???  Ok ok ok .....53.....monster fish man!
Congradulations on your 53by23 inch muskie, a very healthy clean lookin fish that dont come around as often as we wish but certainly make the day when they do
